This is different from the Java code, where for each slime, the next variable starts at size-1 again. Wait, in the Java code:

for (int slime : active) {
    int next = size - 1;
    while (next >=0 && (S[next] >= slime || spawned[next])) {
        next--;
    }
    ...
} So for each slime in active, the next variable starts at size-1 and decrements. So each slime's search starts from the end of the array. But in the Fortran code as written, next_idx is initialized to size_val once before processing all slimes. So after processing one slime, next_idx is left at some index, and the next slime's search starts from there, which may be incorrect. Ah, that's a critical error.
